    "recap_url": "https://www.LibertyFlames.com/news/2026/3/20/baseball-liberty-strikes-in-the-10th-for-2-0-win-over-kennesaw-state",
    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "KENNESAW, GA. \u2013\nCenter fielder\nJosh Campos\nbelted a home run and designated hitter\nJordan Jaffe\nhad an RBI single in the 10\nth\ninnings to push the Liberty Flames past the Kennesaw State Owls 2-0 in the opening game of a three-game CUSA series Friday night at Mickey Dunn Stadium.\nScoreless after nine innings, Liberty jumped on reliever Harry Cain, who had pitched three scoreless innings entering the 10\nth\ninning. Campos launched a 1-2 pitch from the right-hander over the left field wall to put the Flames in front 1-0. Two batters later, right fielder\nRyan Drumm\ndropped a double down the right field line and came around to score Liberty's second run on a single back up the middle by Jaffe.\nFlames starter\nBen Blair\nand relievers\nTyler August\nand\nJosh Swink\ncombined to allow three hits over 10 scoreless innings.\nCampos was one of three Flames with two hits in the contest.\nLiberty evens its record to 2-2 in CUSA play and 14-7 overall. Kennesaw State drops to 1-3 in CUSA and 9-9 overall.\nBox Score Highlights\nRecords:\nLiberty (14-7, 2-2 CUSA); Kennesaw State (9-9, 1-3 CUSA)\nLocation:\nMickey Dunn Stadium (Kennesaw, Ga.)\nWP:\nTyler August\n(2-0) \u00a0|\nLP:\nHarry Cain (2-1) |\nSV:\nJosh Swink\n(2)\nScoring Summary\n10\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Campos homers, 1-0\n10\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Jaffe singles, Drumm scores, 2-0\nNotable Numbers\n- Liberty outhit Kennesaw State, 9-3, in the contest. Neither team committed an error.\n- The Flames left 10 men on base. The Owls left eight.\n- Shortstop\nTanner Marsh\nand third baseman\nJaxon Sorenson\njoined Campos with two hits apiece in the game.\n- Liberty starting pitcher\nBen Blair\npitched seven scoreless innings but did not figure in the decision. He allowed three hits. He struck out eight and walked one. He stranded the lone Owl runner that managed to get to third with one out in the fifth.\n- August took over in the eighth and picked up the win. The right-hander pitched 2 2/3 innings of relief. He did not give up a hit, striking out four and walking three.\n- Swink came in with two Owls on base and two out in the 10\nth\n. He proceeded to retire the only batter he faced to record a save.\n- Cain takes the loss for Kennesaw State. The reliever, the second of three Owls to pitch in the game, gave up two runs on four hits over 4 1/3 innings. He struck out nine and walked one.\n- No Kennesaw State batter had more than one hit in the contest.\n-\nBeyond the Box Score\n- Today's contest was the 29\nth\nmeeting between the Flames and the Owls. Liberty has played Kennesaw State more than any other Conference USA team in its history.\n- With two hits in the game, Marsh collected his team-leading eighth multi-hit game. Meanwhile, Sorenson recorded his fourth multi-hit game in the contest.\n- Jaffe has at least one hit in each of his last seven games\n- Flames first baseman\nRiley DeCandido\nwalked three times in the game. He has now reached base in each of his last 10 games.\n- Blair walked his first batter since Feb. 27 in a 7-2 win over Hofstra, a span of 16 2/3 innings. The right-hander has struck out 50 and walked four over 35 1/3 innings this season.\n- August has not allowed a run during his last six appearances.\nUp Next\nThe Flames and the Owls will meet again in the middle game of their CUSA series tomorrow at Mickey Dunn Stadium. The first pitch is scheduled for 4 p.m.\nMake No Mistake! That 1 is Gone!\nJosh Campos\nputs the Flames in front! ??\npic.twitter.com/IgE5PZstzF\n\u2014 Liberty Baseball (@LibertyBaseball)\nMarch 21, 2026",
